title: 10 gallon Fish Tank with Betta and ALL accessories
post:
Hello, due to personal circumstances I am unable to keep my tanks and am looking for a good home for my fish. I am asking for an adoption fee but my preference will be someone who knows how to care for fish over someone able to offer more. I have two tanks - a 10 gallon with a male betta and a 20 gallon with 5 cloud mountain minnows and 2 upside-down catfish. 

10 gallon with Blue Male Betta
Comes with:

Short list:
Male blue betta (his name is Bellamy but I have a feeling he doesn't know it so feel free to give him a new one)
Elive Aqua Duo 10 Gallon tank
Glass top
Elive filter (with live plant option)
Cascade 300 filter 
1 extra filter cartridge 
Decky aquarium light (adjustable + customizable)   + remote
50 W Heater w/ guard
Thermometer 
Ceramic bridge decor 
Bioactive substrate 
Two anubias 
Long tweezers
Stress coat+ (makes tap water safe)
Extra light 
Timer (not sure if this works)
3 betta food varieties 
Vacation feeders (I don't recommend these save for emergencies - if you can get someone to care for your fish that's best) 
Net 
Tank siphon Vacuum

Longer explanations of items:

Dimensiona of the tank are (in inches) 20l, 11 3/4h, 10 1/4w

The Elive filter has Expanded clay as media. You can take off the top and Plant a fish-safe plant (for example bamboo, wheatgrass, basil, peace lily, pothos, Arrowhead plant [happy to offer a cutting of this] lucky bamboo, thyme, catnip, mint, cilantro, peppers, green beans, lettuce, micro greens, and more) which will remove pollutants from the water and act as a natural filter. 

I personally felt that wouldn't be enough filtration so I added the Cascade 300 with physical, chemical, and biological underwater filtration. It also ensures there's not too much current for delicate fish like Bettas since you can turn the output to the glass. 

Long tweezers (for planting or moving lighter things mostly)

Thermometer (simple sticker kind)

Heater 

Deckey aquarium light RGB Multi-color LED lights for 14.8-20.6incg fish tank extendable light 36LED 8W + IR Remote controller 
(this is a really nice light. It has sooooo many options for color and brightness and patterns. I tend to only use a white or yellow light and on special occasions the slow changing of colors. I think the crazy strobe stuff would be stressful for the fish so I don't recommend using those settings on the tank.)

His current foods are pellets, flakes, and longer bits. He isn't too fond of freeze dried bloodworms suprisingly but likes other treats.

Tank siphon vacuum - for cleaning 

I have paper on the back of the tank to make things look more finished and stop light from getting in from behind. It's easily removable.  

Unfortunately Bellamy does have torn fins at the moment from a mishap with Seiryu stone (which has since been removed from his tank) but he is recovering quickly with medication.

Please message me if you're interested and have an offer. This would be everything needed. Willing to drive to a public space near you.

Ideally looking for people who either have done research or already have fish experience and are willing to put in maintenance to take care of these beautiful little creatures.

title: 20 gallon Fish Tank with all Accessories + cloud mountain minnows ansh
post:
Hello, due to personal circumstances I am unable to keep my tanks and am looking for a good home for my fish. I am asking for an adoption fee but my preference will be someone who knows how to care for fish/is willing to learn over someone able to offer more. I have two tanks - a 10 gallon with a male betta and a 20 gallon with 5 cloud mountain minnows and 2 upside-down catfish.  

The 20gallon tank comes with 
Short list:

5 cloud mountain minnows and 2 upside-down catfish 
20 gallon tank 
Stand
Aqua-tech 20-40 filter
1 extra filter cartridge 
Seachem flourish glue 
Wooden fake tree on stone
Red Lavarock 
A few live plants 
Aquarium air pump (good for shrimp) 
Seachem Prime - concentrated conditioner for marine and freshwater 500ml/16.9fl oz
Seachem stress guard 500ml/16.9fl oz
Seachem stability - new tank stabilization system for marine and freshwater 500ml/16.9fl oz
Ammonia clear 2 tabs
Freshwater aquarium/fish safe plant fertilizer
10 day feeder
3 Seiryu stones 
Long tweezers
24'' fluorescent tank light with cover 
Thermometer 
API Freshwater Master test kit 
Net
Bamboo toothbrush for cleaning 
Topfin algea cleaning razor 
ph down 
3 food types 
Tank siphon vacuum


More explanatory list: 

5 cloud mountain minnows and 2 upside-down catfish. The catfish are at least 10 years old now and they are nocturnal and hide most of the time. The minnows are at least 3 years old - two are the yellow variation. 

20 gallon tank - 24 (l) x 16 1/2 (h) x 12 1/4 (w)
+ Aqua-tech 20-40 filter
+ Stand

All-glass aquarium Inc 24'' fluorescent aquarium reflector/light - 120v, 19 watt, 60hz. These bulbs last for years. Some salt buildup on the clear plastic  but it doesn't effect anything. 

APC power saving surge protector with many timers (this allows you to have the light and whatever else you plug into the 4 slots turn off/on on a timer. Has many timer options.) 

Seachem flourish glue - this is aquarium safe glue if you're doing a little DIY 

Wooden fake tree on stone - if you put moss on this it looks like cute mini tree and is blends in on the lava rock. 

Red Lavarock - this is actually really valuable. Pieces this size go upwards of $50 each at times. I think I got them all for $70. Plants love rooting into them, especially anubias (which don't like actual substrate). 

A few live plants (2 anubias who do not react super well to big water changes so they may be a bit worse for wear.)

Aquarium air pump (good for shrimp and some other fish.)

Seachem Prime - concentrated conditioner for marine and freshwater 500ml/16.9fl oz
Seachem stress guard 500ml/16.9fl oz
Seachem stability - new tank stabilization system for marine and freshwater 500ml/16.9fl oz
Ammonia clear 2 tabs (should only be used in emergencies. Regular water changes and using stability as directed should render this unecessary) 
10 day feeder (should only to be used in emergencies as well, not great on tanks or fish)
3 Seiryu stones (another very valuable hardscaping rock. These are about medium sized.) 
24'' fluorescent tank light with cover 
Thermometer (the sticker kind)
API Freshwater Master test kit (super useful! Also worth $30.)
Net
Bamboo toothbrush for cleaning rocks
Topfin algea cleaning razor 
Ph down liquid
3 food types - shrimp pellets, and two types of tropical flakes 
Tank siphon Vacuum (used to clean the tank) 

I have paper on the back of the tank to make things look more finished and stop light from getting in from behind. It's easily removable. 


Please message me if you're interested and have an offer.
This would be everything needed. Willing to drive to a public space near you.
Ideally looking for people who either have done research or already have fish experience and are willing to put in maintenance to take care of these beautiful little creatures.

title: Rehoming our dogs
post: We have 2 lab/boxers that are 5 years old. Brothers born together, have never been separated. They are very friendly, sweet, mellow, obedient and house trained. They do everything the same, move in unison. They are great with children!! They rarely bark and are not hyper at all. They are just wonderful family members. We both work long days and feel terrible that they are alone a lot.  Being in a family that is around a bit more is what they need. They have all their shots current. They must go together. Please only contact if you want to provide a loving home! Thank you.
